<recipe>
<title>
Almond Joy Cookies
</title>
<details>
AUTHOR: i heart eating
PREP TIME: 2 hours 15 minutes
COOK TIME: 8 minutes
TOTAL TIME: 2 hours 23 minutes
COURSE: Dessert
CUISINE: American
KEYWORD: almond, chocolate chip, coconut, cookie
SERVINGS: 30
</details>
<ingredients>
3 cups all-purpose flour
1 teaspoon baking soda
3/4 teaspoon kosher salt
1/2 cup butter at cool room temperature
1/2 cup plain vegetable shortening
1 cup brown sugar packed
1/2 cup granulated sugar
2 large eggs
1 1/2 teaspoons almond extract
1 teaspoon vanilla extract
1 cup semisweet chocolate chips
1/2 cup sweetened shredded coconut
1/2 cup sliced almonds
</ingredients>
<instructions>
In a small bowl, whisk together flour, baking soda, and salt. Set aside.
In a large bowl, beat together butter and shortening until well-combined.
Add sugars, and beat for about 4-5 minutes on high, or until very well-combined.
Add eggs, one at a time, and then almond and vanilla extracts; beat in for 3 minutes.
Stir in flour mixture until just combined.
Add chocolate chips, coconut, and almonds; stir in.
Cover, and refrigerate dough for at least 2 hours.
Preheat oven to 375 F, and line 2 baking sheets with parchment paper.
Drop dough by medium scoops (1.5 tablespoons) onto prepared cookie sheets.
Bake for about 8-12 minutes, or until very lightly browned at the edges.
Let cool on baking sheet.
</instructions>
</recipe>
